<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n30160f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30160f">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30160f"> 160(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> soldier sleeps standing</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Sir Philip Gibbs, in his account of the retreat from Mons, thus describes this sort of thing: &ldquo;Being attacked was the only thing that kept them awake. Towards the end of this fighting they had a drunken craving for sleep, and <mark>they slept standing</mark>, with their heads falling over the parapet <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <small> D. F. Fraser-Harris, <a name="FHMS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FHMS"><cite title="source">Morpheus, or: The Future of Sleep</cite></a> (1928) 21</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c13239d" href="c13all.htm#c13239d">VI.C.13:239(d)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
